I"À<p>Galleries can be easily generated in two steps:</p>

<ul>
  <li>define a gallery in the front-matter of your post in the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">galleries</code> object. The gallery
must have the properties <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">name</code> and <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">files</code>. Each file is the path (relative to the current article)
to an image.</li>
</ul>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code>---
galleries:
- name: my-gallery-name
  file:
    - relative/path/to/image.jpg
    - other_image.png
---
</code></pre></div></div>

<ul>
  <li>include the gallery in your post using the template <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">gallery.html</code>. Make sure to the <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">gallery=</code>
parameter and use the name that was defined in front-matter.</li>
</ul>

<div class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge"><div class="highlight"><pre class="highlight"><code> \\like this: { % include gallery.html gallery="my-gallery-name" % }
</code></pre></div></div>

<p>Here is the result, Each thumbnail links to the full image:</p>

